                    <span>Now with the so-called "Curse" now (thankfully) gone, this tripe of a book must be Dan's swan song - his whole career at the Boston Globe has revolved around the "Curse" and his shameless coverage of it.
<br />Dan is a whining wanna-be baseball player who can't put two complete sentences together without mentioning Babe Ruth or Bucky Dent.
<br />If you want to read a good review of the Red Sox' World Series victory, check out Stewart O'Nan & Stephen King's "Faithful".</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">AN ABSOLUTE ABOMINATION</div>
