                    <span>Shaughnessy's gravy train has finally left the station and this book is one last desperate attempt to milk the cash cow of the supposed "curse." Maybe Shaughnessy will now turn his attention to his long-anticipated autobiography "The Curse of the Talentless Hack," in which he explains to the reader how to write the same newspaper column over and over again for 20 years and still get paid for it. Now that the Sox and Patriots are champions, Shaughnessy will probably cook up the "Curse of John Havlicek" for the Celtics or the "Curse of Phil Esposito," for the Bruins" so he will have an excuse to write another lame book.</span>
                  
              
